<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-27T14:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-27T14:41:00-05:00" n="736" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2028.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Saltillo</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-27T13:00:00-06:41"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                        1911—1 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Yesterday the State leader of Coahuila elected Oscar Garza, a banker,
                            provisional governor, but Madero insisted upon election of Carranza, who
                            was chosen this morning.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Voetter.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>